flowRoot.flowPara: You must ensure that the object lifeline of the slot being invoked is an atomic change. That is to say, between the O and the X you must have restored the state of the class to a point where any of it's slots can be called. Queues work best, and Qt handles queues transparently for you via signals/slots. .If all your slots ensure that between O and X the state of the class is restored, they are thread safe.

The exit signal is optional, but you are encouraged to use one when you can to help automate asynchronous designs. They are usually just one extra click and drag. There is a use-case exit to actor signal too, and it is "optional but recommended" as well.
